  <p class="lead">Day 6: A Hail Mary</p>
  <p>The past few days had been a bloodbath and only a few townsfolk remained. Prospects for Joistown civilization had been lost and it was decided the final showdown would take place in a cage match centred on the square. Loose boards and barrels, and all kinds of rubble were piled high at the square's exits and lit ablaze. There was no escape. Kill or be killed.</p>
  <p>The fighting was fierce in this apocalyptic setting, and Dave & Dennis found themselves positioned to the middle of the other four pairs.</p>
  <p>"Give it up Dave, and you too Dennis! Show us your true form already so that we might see you laid to rest as you truly are!" declared Kota. Katz backed him up, "Yeah!"</p>
  <p>Dave & Dennis fired back, "You're evil, all of you. We're no werewolves, it must be one of you!"</p>
  <p>D&D were set upon and smashed to the cobblestone, deader than dead.</p>
  <p>Boisterous laughing filled the flaming square. Ryan, Sandeep, Shaider, and Sharon all transformed. They grew, and sprouted whiskers and long fangs. Dami looked on horrified.</p>
  <p>Sharon grabbed Kota and Sandeep bit into Katz. They died gruesomely as Ryan and Shaider moved in on Dami. Dami whirled out his bow and arrow and slayed Shaider in a single shot right between the eyes. Sharon ROARRED and lunged, but was lashed aside by Dami's whipping of his bow. He loosed another arrow to Sharon' heart.</p>
  <p>The only townsfolk standing at this point were Dami, and Ryan & Sandeep. The two werewolves rushed Dami and had their final snack before moving onto the next village.</p>
  <p>THE END.</p>
